style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Editing the key information of an empire is
accomplished from the Empire Details tab of the Edit Empire screen.<o:p></o=
:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>From here you can cha=
nge an
empire&#8217;s name, dominant race, style of government, cash on hand, empi=
re
colors and flag. You can also adjust their reputation and level of war
weariness.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In the list of Other =
Empires
you can alter the relationship between this empire and any other empire in =
the
galaxy. To change a relationship click on the Relationship column in the row
and select the new relationship type from the dropdown list.<o:p></o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Double-clicking on a
relationship will open a small Alliance panel, allowing you to name a speci=
al
alliance and optionally also lock the relationship. This allows you to setu=
p a
locked, named alliance between multiple empires.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You can also change t=
he
amount of bias an empire displays towards any other empire. Bias influences=
 the
relationship one empire has with another: positive bias makes them naturally
like the other empire, negative bias makes them naturally dislike the other
empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

